---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '@/components/sections/PageHero.astro';
import NarrativeSection from '@/components/sections/NarrativeSection.astro';
import Section from '@/components/ui/Section.astro';
import FocusGrid from '@/components/sections/FocusGrid.astro';
import PrinciplesGrid from '@/components/sections/PrinciplesGrid.astro';
import CallToActionBand from '@/components/sections/CallToActionBand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Background, throughline, and current focus — protocol design, infrastructure, real-time ML, writing, and formal research."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About"
    title="About"
    body="I work on systems that need to remain credible under pressure."
  />

  <NarrativeSection>
    <p>
      My background sits at the intersection of protocol design, infrastructure, real-time machine
      learning, and long-form research. On the engineering side, that has meant building
      privacy-preserving and adversarial systems, working on distributed ML pipelines, and shipping
      real-time detection systems in operational settings. On the research and writing side, it has
      meant trying to articulate what happens to trust, coordination, and value when verification
      remains expensive but persuasion and forgery become cheap.
    </p>
    <p>
      Recent public-facing work includes distributed LLM fine-tuning in TS/SCI environments,
      real-time underwater detection work supporting Navy follow-on programs, AfterFiat, and two
      peer-reviewed papers spanning music generation and astrophysical sonification.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm most interested in systems that do not assume benign conditions. That includes threat
      modeling, incentive design, production operations, and the design of mechanisms that remain
      legible and resilient when the surrounding environment becomes noisy, strategic, or
      adversarial. In practice, that has included work across decentralized storage protocols,
      distributed LLM fine-tuning, real-time underwater detection, and formal research in music and
      sonification.
    </p>
    <p>
      A second thread running through all of this is form. I studied music formally before moving
      into computer science, and I still think in terms of structure, counterpoint, invariants,
      tension, and resolution. That is one reason my work tends to move across engineering, writing,
      and research without feeling discontinuous to me: they are all, at some level, questions about
      signal, pattern, and coordination.
    </p>
  </NarrativeSection>

  <Section>
    <h2>What I Work On</h2>
    <ul class="work-list" role="list">
      <li>Protocol and infrastructure design</li>
      <li>Distributed systems and production ML</li>
      <li>Real-time detection and edge inference</li>
      <li>Writing on verification, repression, and synthetic media</li>
      <li>Research in music, sonification, and formal structure</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <FocusGrid />
  <PrinciplesGrid />

  <CallToActionBand
    heading="Explore the work"
    body="From engineering case studies to published research and long-form writing."
    actions={[
      { label: 'View Work', href: '/work', variant: 'primary' },
      { label: 'Read Research', href: '/research', variant: 'secondary' },
      { label: 'Get in Touch', href: '/contact', variant: 'secondary' },
    ]}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    margin-top: var(--sp-6);
  }

  .work-list li {
    font: var(--text-body);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    padding-left: var(--sp-4);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-brass);
  }
</style>
